==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indophenol
<hw>In`do*phe"nol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ind</ets>igo + <ets>phenol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a series of artificial blue dyestuffs, resembling indigo
in appearance, and obtained by the action of phenol on certain
nitrogenous derivatives of quinone. Simple indophenol proper, the parent
compound of the dye series, is a quinonimine derivative with the formula
<chform>C12H9NO2</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indorsable</ent>⟦br⟧
